54// The ratio between kVTCompressionPropertyKey_DataRateLimits and
55// kVTCompressionPropertyKey_AverageBitRate. The data rate limit is set higher
56// than the average bit rate to avoid undershooting the target.
57const float kLimitToAverageBitRateFactor = 1.5f;
58// These thresholds deviate from the default h265 QP thresholds, as they
59// have been found to work better on devices that support VideoToolbox
60const int kLowh265QpThreshold = 28;
61const int kHighh265QpThreshold = 39;
62
63// Struct that we pass to the encoder per frame to encode. We receive it again
64// in the encoder callback.
65struct API_AVAILABLE(ios(11.0)) RTCFrameEncodeParams {
66 RTCFrameEncodeParams(RTCVideoEncoderH265* e,
67 int32_t w,
68 int32_t h,
69 int64_t rtms,
70 uint32_t ts,
71 RTCVideoRotation r)
72 : encoder(e),
73 width(w),
74 height(h),
75 render_time_ms(rtms),
76 timestamp(ts),
77 rotation(r) {}
78
79 RTCVideoEncoderH265* encoder;
80 int32_t width;
81 int32_t height;
82 int64_t render_time_ms;
83 uint32_t timestamp;
84 RTCVideoRotation rotation;
85};
86
87// We receive I420Frames as input, but we need to feed CVPixelBuffers into the
88// encoder. This performs the copy and format conversion.
89// TODO(tkchin): See if encoder will accept i420 frames and compare performance.
90bool CopyVideoFrameToPixelBuffer(id<RTCI420Buffer> frameBuffer,
91 CVPixelBufferRef pixelBuffer) {
92 RTC_DCHECK(pixelBuffer);
93 RTC_DCHECK_EQ(CVPixelBufferGetPixelFormatType(pixelBuffer),
94 kCVPixelFormatType_420YpCbCr8BiPlanarFullRange);
95 RTC_DCHECK_EQ(CVPixelBufferGetHeightOfPlane(pixelBuffer, 0),
96 frameBuffer.height);
97 RTC_DCHECK_EQ(CVPixelBufferGetWidthOfPlane(pixelBuffer, 0),
98 frameBuffer.width);
99
100 CVReturn cvRet = CVPixelBufferLockBaseAddress(pixelBuffer, 0);
101 if (cvRet != kCVReturnSuccess) {
102 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << "Failed to lock base address: " << cvRet;
103 return false;
104 }
105
106 uint8_t* dstY = reinterpret_cast<uint8_t*>(
107 CVPixelBufferGetBaseAddressOfPlane(pixelBuffer, 0));
108 int dstStrideY = CVPixelBufferGetBytesPerRowOfPlane(pixelBuffer, 0);
109 uint8_t* dstUV = reinterpret_cast<uint8_t*>(
110 CVPixelBufferGetBaseAddressOfPlane(pixelBuffer, 1));
111 int dstStrideUV = CVPixelBufferGetBytesPerRowOfPlane(pixelBuffer, 1);
112 // Convert I420 to NV12.
113 int ret = libyuv::I420ToNV12(
114 frameBuffer.dataY, frameBuffer.strideY, frameBuffer.dataU,
115 frameBuffer.strideU, frameBuffer.dataV, frameBuffer.strideV, dstY,
116 dstStrideY, dstUV, dstStrideUV, frameBuffer.width, frameBuffer.height);
117 CVPixelBufferUnlockBaseAddress(pixelBuffer, 0);
118 if (ret) {
119 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << "Error converting I420 VideoFrame to NV12 :" << ret;
120 return false;
121 }
122 return true;
123}
124
125CVPixelBufferRef CreatePixelBuffer(CVPixelBufferPoolRef pixel_buffer_pool) {
126 if (!pixel_buffer_pool) {
127 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << "Failed to get pixel buffer pool.";
128 return nullptr;
129 }
130 CVPixelBufferRef pixel_buffer;
131 CVReturn ret = CVPixelBufferPoolCreatePixelBuffer(nullptr, pixel_buffer_pool,
132 &pixel_buffer);
133 if (ret != kCVReturnSuccess) {
134 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << "Failed to create pixel buffer: " << ret;
135 // We probably want to drop frames here, since failure probably means
136 // that the pool is empty.
137 return nullptr;
138 }
139 return pixel_buffer;
140}
141
142// This is the callback function that VideoToolbox calls when encode is
143// complete. From inspection this happens on its own queue.
144void compressionOutputCallback(void* encoder,
145 void* params,
146 OSStatus status,
147 VTEncodeInfoFlags infoFlags,
148 CMSampleBufferRef sampleBuffer)
149 API_AVAILABLE(ios(11.0)) {
150 RTC_CHECK(params);
151 std::unique_ptr<RTCFrameEncodeParams> encodeParams(
152 reinterpret_cast<RTCFrameEncodeParams*>(params));
153 RTC_CHECK(encodeParams->encoder);
154 [encodeParams->encoder frameWasEncoded:status
155 flags:infoFlags
156 sampleBuffer:sampleBuffer
157 width:encodeParams->width
158 height:encodeParams->height
159 renderTimeMs:encodeParams->render_time_ms
160 timestamp:encodeParams->timestamp
161 rotation:encodeParams->rotation];
162}

165@implementation RTCVideoEncoderH265 {
166 RTCVideoCodecInfo* _codecInfo;
167 std::unique_ptr<webrtc::BitrateAdjuster> _bitrateAdjuster;
168 uint32_t _targetBitrateBps;
169 uint32_t _encoderBitrateBps;
170 CFStringRef _profile;
171 RTCVideoEncoderCallback _callback;
172 int32_t _width;
173 int32_t _height;
174 VTCompressionSessionRef _compressionSession;
175 RTCVideoCodecMode _mode;
176 int framesLeft;
177
178 std::vector<uint8_t> _nv12ScaleBuffer;
179}

181// .5 is set as a mininum to prevent overcompensating for large temporary
182// overshoots. We don't want to degrade video quality too badly.
183// .95 is set to prevent oscillations. When a lower bitrate is set on the
184// encoder than previously set, its output seems to have a brief period of
185// drastically reduced bitrate, so we want to avoid that. In steady state
186// conditions, 0.95 seems to give us better overall bitrate over long periods
187// of time.
188- (instancetype)initWithCodecInfo:(RTCVideoCodecInfo*)codecInfo {
189 if (self = [super init]) {
190 _codecInfo = codecInfo;
191 _bitrateAdjuster.reset(new webrtc::BitrateAdjuster(.5, .95));
192 RTC_CHECK([codecInfo.name isEqualToString:@"H265"]);
193 }
194 return self;
195}
196
197- (void)dealloc {
198 [self destroyCompressionSession];
199}
200
201- (NSInteger)startEncodeWithSettings:(RTCVideoEncoderSettings*)settings
202 numberOfCores:(int)numberOfCores {
203 RTC_DCHECK(settings);
204 RTC_DCHECK([settings.name isEqualToString:@"H265"]);
205
206 _width = settings.width;
207 _height = settings.height;
208 _mode = settings.mode;
209
210 // We can only set average bitrate on the HW encoder.
211 _targetBitrateBps = settings.startBitrate;
212 _bitrateAdjuster->SetTargetBitrateBps(_targetBitrateBps);
213
214 return [self resetCompressionSession];
215}
216
217- (NSInteger)encode:(RTCVideoFrame*)frame
218 codecSpecificInfo:(id<RTCCodecSpecificInfo>)codecSpecificInfo
219 frameTypes:(NSArray<NSNumber*>*)frameTypes {
220 RTC_DCHECK_EQ(frame.width, _width);
221 RTC_DCHECK_EQ(frame.height, _height);
222 if (!_callback || !_compressionSession) {
223 return WEBRTC_VIDEO_CODEC_UNINITIALIZED;
224 }
225 BOOL isKeyframeRequired = NO;
226
227 // Get a pixel buffer from the pool and copy frame data over.
228 CVPixelBufferPoolRef pixelBufferPool =
229 VTCompressionSessionGetPixelBufferPool(_compressionSession);
230
231#if defined(WEBRTC_IOS)
232 if (!pixelBufferPool) {
233 // Kind of a hack. On backgrounding, the compression session seems to get
234 // invalidated, which causes this pool call to fail when the application
235 // is foregrounded and frames are being sent for encoding again.
236 // Resetting the session when this happens fixes the issue.
237 // In addition we request a keyframe so video can recover quickly.
238 [self resetCompressionSession];
239 pixelBufferPool =
240 VTCompressionSessionGetPixelBufferPool(_compressionSession);
241 isKeyframeRequired = YES;
242 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << "Resetting compression session due to invalid pool.";
243 }
244#endif
245
246 CVPixelBufferRef pixelBuffer = nullptr;
247 if ([frame.buffer isKindOfClass:[RTCCVPixelBuffer class]]) {
248 // Native frame buffer
249 RTCCVPixelBuffer* rtcPixelBuffer = (RTCCVPixelBuffer*)frame.buffer;
250 if (![rtcPixelBuffer requiresCropping]) {
251 // This pixel buffer might have a higher resolution than what the
252 // compression session is configured to. The compression session can
253 // handle that and will output encoded frames in the configured
254 // resolution regardless of the input pixel buffer resolution.
255 pixelBuffer = rtcPixelBuffer.pixelBuffer;
256 CVBufferRetain(pixelBuffer);
257 } else {
258 // Cropping required, we need to crop and scale to a new pixel buffer.
259 pixelBuffer = CreatePixelBuffer(pixelBufferPool);
260 if (!pixelBuffer) {
261 return WEBRTC_VIDEO_CODEC_ERROR;
262 }
263 int dstWidth = CVPixelBufferGetWidth(pixelBuffer);
264 int dstHeight = CVPixelBufferGetHeight(pixelBuffer);
265 if ([rtcPixelBuffer requiresScalingToWidth:dstWidth height:dstHeight]) {
266 int size =
267 [rtcPixelBuffer bufferSizeForCroppingAndScalingToWidth:dstWidth
268 height:dstHeight];
269 _nv12ScaleBuffer.resize(size);
270 } else {
271 _nv12ScaleBuffer.clear();
272 }
273 _nv12ScaleBuffer.shrink_to_fit();
274 if (![rtcPixelBuffer cropAndScaleTo:pixelBuffer
275 withTempBuffer:_nv12ScaleBuffer.data()]) {
276 return WEBRTC_VIDEO_CODEC_ERROR;
277 }
278 }
279 }
280
281 if (!pixelBuffer) {
282 // We did not have a native frame buffer
283 pixelBuffer = CreatePixelBuffer(pixelBufferPool);
284 if (!pixelBuffer) {
285 return WEBRTC_VIDEO_CODEC_ERROR;
286 }
287 RTC_DCHECK(pixelBuffer);
288 if (!CopyVideoFrameToPixelBuffer([frame.buffer toI420], pixelBuffer)) {
289 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << "Failed to copy frame data.";
290 CVBufferRelease(pixelBuffer);
291 return WEBRTC_VIDEO_CODEC_ERROR;
292 }
293 }
294
295 // Check if we need a keyframe.
296 if (!isKeyframeRequired && frameTypes) {
297 for (NSNumber* frameType in frameTypes) {
298 if ((RTCFrameType)frameType.intValue == RTCFrameTypeVideoFrameKey) {
299 isKeyframeRequired = YES;
300 break;
301 }
302 }
303 }
304
305 CMTime presentationTimeStamp =
306 CMTimeMake(frame.timeStampNs / rtc::kNumNanosecsPerMillisec, 1000);
307 CFDictionaryRef frameProperties = nullptr;
308 if (isKeyframeRequired) {
309 CFTypeRef keys[] = {kVTEncodeFrameOptionKey_ForceKeyFrame};
310 CFTypeRef values[] = {kCFBooleanTrue};
311 frameProperties = CreateCFTypeDictionary(keys, values, 1);
312 }
313
314 std::unique_ptr<RTCFrameEncodeParams> encodeParams;
315 encodeParams.reset(new RTCFrameEncodeParams(
316 self, _width, _height, frame.timeStampNs / rtc::kNumNanosecsPerMillisec,
317 frame.timeStamp, frame.rotation));
318
319 // Update the bitrate if needed.
320 [self setBitrateBps:_bitrateAdjuster->GetAdjustedBitrateBps()];
321
322 OSStatus status = VTCompressionSessionEncodeFrame(
323 _compressionSession, pixelBuffer, presentationTimeStamp, kCMTimeInvalid,
324 frameProperties, encodeParams.release(), nullptr);
325 if (frameProperties) {
326 CFRelease(frameProperties);
327 }
328 if (pixelBuffer) {
329 CVBufferRelease(pixelBuffer);
330 }
331 if (status != noErr) {
332 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << "Failed to encode frame with code: " << status;
333 return WEBRTC_VIDEO_CODEC_ERROR;
334 }
335 return WEBRTC_VIDEO_CODEC_OK;
336}
337
338- (void)setCallback:(RTCVideoEncoderCallback)callback {
339 _callback = callback;
340}

342- (int)setBitrate:(uint32_t)bitrateKbit framerate:(uint32_t)framerate {
343 _targetBitrateBps = 1000 * bitrateKbit;
344 _bitrateAdjuster->SetTargetBitrateBps(_targetBitrateBps);
345 [self setBitrateBps:_bitrateAdjuster->GetAdjustedBitrateBps()];
346 return WEBRTC_VIDEO_CODEC_OK;
347}

349#pragma mark - Private

351- (NSInteger)releaseEncoder {
352 // Need to destroy so that the session is invalidated and won't use the
353 // callback anymore. Do not remove callback until the session is invalidated
354 // since async encoder callbacks can occur until invalidation.
355 [self destroyCompressionSession];
356 _callback = nullptr;
357 return WEBRTC_VIDEO_CODEC_OK;
358}
359
360- (int)resetCompressionSession {
361 [self destroyCompressionSession];
362
363 // Set source image buffer attributes. These attributes will be present on
364 // buffers retrieved from the encoder's pixel buffer pool.
365 const size_t attributesSize = 3;
366 CFTypeRef keys[attributesSize] = {
367#if defined(WEBRTC_MAC) || defined(WEBRTC_MAC_CATALYST)
368 kCVPixelBufferOpenGLCompatibilityKey,
369#elif defined(WEBRTC_IOS)
370 kCVPixelBufferOpenGLESCompatibilityKey,
371#endif
372 kCVPixelBufferIOSurfacePropertiesKey,
373 kCVPixelBufferPixelFormatTypeKey
374 };
375 CFDictionaryRef ioSurfaceValue = CreateCFTypeDictionary(nullptr, nullptr, 0);
376 int64_t nv12type = kCVPixelFormatType_420YpCbCr8BiPlanarFullRange;
377 CFNumberRef pixelFormat =
378 CFNumberCreate(nullptr, kCFNumberLongType, &nv12type);
379 CFTypeRef values[attributesSize] = {kCFBooleanTrue, ioSurfaceValue,
380 pixelFormat};
381 CFDictionaryRef sourceAttributes =
382 CreateCFTypeDictionary(keys, values, attributesSize);
383 if (ioSurfaceValue) {
384 CFRelease(ioSurfaceValue);
385 ioSurfaceValue = nullptr;
386 }
387 if (pixelFormat) {
388 CFRelease(pixelFormat);
389 pixelFormat = nullptr;
390 }
391 CFMutableDictionaryRef encoder_specs = CFDictionaryCreateMutable(nullptr, 2, &kCFTypeDictionaryKeyCallBacks, &kCFTypeDictionaryValueCallBacks);
392#if defined(WEBRTC_MAC) && !defined(WEBRTC_IOS)
393 CFDictionarySetValue(encoder_specs, kVTVideoEncoderSpecification_EnableHardwareAcceleratedVideoEncoder, kCFBooleanTrue);
394#endif
395#if HAVE_VTB_REQUIREDLOWLATENCY
396 // We will want to enable this property once working.
397 // CFDictionarySetValue(encoder_specs, kVTVideoEncoderSpecification_RequiredLowLatency, kCFBooleanTrue);
398#endif
399 OSStatus status = VTCompressionSessionCreate(
400 nullptr, // use default allocator
401 _width, _height, kCMVideoCodecType_HEVC,
402 encoder_specs, // use hardware accelerated encoder if available
403 sourceAttributes,
404 nullptr, // use default compressed data allocator
405 compressionOutputCallback, nullptr, &_compressionSession);
406 if (sourceAttributes) {
407 CFRelease(sourceAttributes);
408 sourceAttributes = nullptr;
409 }
410 if (encoder_specs) {
411 CFRelease(encoder_specs);
412 encoder_specs = nullptr;
413 }
414 if (status != noErr) {
415 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << "Failed to create compression session: " << status;
416 return WEBRTC_VIDEO_CODEC_ERROR;
417 }
418#if defined(WEBRTC_MAC) && !defined(WEBRTC_IOS)
419 CFBooleanRef hwaccl_enabled = nullptr;
420 status = VTSessionCopyProperty(
421 _compressionSession,
422 kVTCompressionPropertyKey_UsingHardwareAcceleratedVideoEncoder, nullptr,
423 &hwaccl_enabled);
424 if (status == noErr && (CFBooleanGetValue(hwaccl_enabled))) {
425 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << "Compression session created with hw accl enabled";
426 } else {
427 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << "Compression session created with hw accl disabled";
428 }
429#endif
430 [self configureCompressionSession];
431 return WEBRTC_VIDEO_CODEC_OK;
432}
433
434- (void)configureCompressionSession {
435 RTC_DCHECK(_compressionSession);
436 SetVTSessionProperty(_compressionSession, nullptr, kVTCompressionPropertyKey_RealTime,
437 false);
438 // SetVTSessionProperty(_compressionSession,
439 // kVTCompressionPropertyKey_ProfileLevel, _profile);
440 SetVTSessionProperty(_compressionSession, nullptr,
441 kVTCompressionPropertyKey_AllowFrameReordering, false);
442 [self setEncoderBitrateBps:_targetBitrateBps];
443
444 // Set a relatively large value for keyframe emission (7200 frames or 4 minutes).
445 SetVTSessionProperty(_compressionSession, nullptr,
446 kVTCompressionPropertyKey_MaxKeyFrameInterval, 7200);
447 SetVTSessionProperty(_compressionSession, nullptr,
448 kVTCompressionPropertyKey_MaxKeyFrameIntervalDuration,
449 240);
450 OSStatus status =
451 VTCompressionSessionPrepareToEncodeFrames(_compressionSession);
452 if (status != noErr) {
453 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << "Compression session failed to prepare encode frames.";
454 }
455}
456
457- (void)destroyCompressionSession {
458 if (_compressionSession) {
459 VTCompressionSessionInvalidate(_compressionSession);
460 CFRelease(_compressionSession);
461 _compressionSession = nullptr;
462 }
463}

469- (void)setBitrateBps:(uint32_t)bitrateBps {
470 if (_encoderBitrateBps != bitrateBps) {
471 [self setEncoderBitrateBps:bitrateBps];
472 }
473}
474
475- (void)setEncoderBitrateBps:(uint32_t)bitrateBps {
476 if (_compressionSession) {
477 SetVTSessionProperty(_compressionSession, nullptr,
478 kVTCompressionPropertyKey_AverageBitRate, bitrateBps);
479
480 // TODO(tkchin): Add a helper method to set array value.
481 int64_t dataLimitBytesPerSecondValue =
482 static_cast<int64_t>(bitrateBps * kLimitToAverageBitRateFactor / 8);
483 CFNumberRef bytesPerSecond =
484 CFNumberCreate(kCFAllocatorDefault, kCFNumberSInt64Type,
485 &dataLimitBytesPerSecondValue);
486 int64_t oneSecondValue = 1;
487 CFNumberRef oneSecond = CFNumberCreate(
488 kCFAllocatorDefault, kCFNumberSInt64Type, &oneSecondValue);
489 const void* nums[2] = {bytesPerSecond, oneSecond};
490 CFArrayRef dataRateLimits =
491 CFArrayCreate(nullptr, nums, 2, &kCFTypeArrayCallBacks);
492 OSStatus status = VTSessionSetProperty(
493 _compressionSession, kVTCompressionPropertyKey_DataRateLimits,
494 dataRateLimits);
495 if (bytesPerSecond) {
496 CFRelease(bytesPerSecond);
497 }
498 if (oneSecond) {
499 CFRelease(oneSecond);
500 }
501 if (dataRateLimits) {
502 CFRelease(dataRateLimits);
503 }
504 if (status != noErr) {
505 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << "Failed to set data rate limit";
506 }
507
508 _encoderBitrateBps = bitrateBps;
509 }
510}
511
512- (void)frameWasEncoded:(OSStatus)status
513 flags:(VTEncodeInfoFlags)infoFlags
514 sampleBuffer:(CMSampleBufferRef)sampleBuffer
515 width:(int32_t)width
516 height:(int32_t)height
517 renderTimeMs:(int64_t)renderTimeMs
518 timestamp:(uint32_t)timestamp
519 rotation:(RTCVideoRotation)rotation {
520 if (status != noErr) {
521 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << "h265 encode failed.";
522 return;
523 }
524 if (infoFlags & kVTEncodeInfo_FrameDropped) {
525 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << "h265 encoder dropped a frame.";
526 return;
527 }
528
529 BOOL isKeyframe = NO;
530 CFArrayRef attachments =
531 CMSampleBufferGetSampleAttachmentsArray(sampleBuffer, 0);
532 if (attachments != nullptr && CFArrayGetCount(attachments)) {
533 CFDictionaryRef attachment =
534 static_cast<CFDictionaryRef>(CFArrayGetValueAtIndex(attachments, 0));
535 isKeyframe =
536 !CFDictionaryContainsKey(attachment, kCMSampleAttachmentKey_NotSync);
537 }
538
539 if (isKeyframe) {
540 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << "Generated keyframe";
541 }
542
543 std::unique_ptr<rtc::Buffer> buffer(new rtc::Buffer());
544 if (!webrtc::H265CMSampleBufferToAnnexBBuffer(sampleBuffer, isKeyframe, buffer.get())) {
545 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << "Unable to parse H265 encoded buffer";
546 }
547
548 RTCEncodedImage* frame = [[RTCEncodedImage alloc] init];
549 frame.buffer = [NSData dataWithBytesNoCopy:buffer->data()
550 length:buffer->size()
551 freeWhenDone:NO];
552 frame.encodedWidth = width;
553 frame.encodedHeight = height;
554 frame.completeFrame = YES;
555 frame.frameType =
556 isKeyframe ? RTCFrameTypeVideoFrameKey : RTCFrameTypeVideoFrameDelta;
557 frame.captureTimeMs = renderTimeMs;
558 frame.timeStamp = timestamp;
559 frame.rotation = rotation;
560 frame.contentType = (_mode == RTCVideoCodecModeScreensharing)
561 ? RTCVideoContentTypeScreenshare
562 : RTCVideoContentTypeUnspecified;
563 frame.flags = webrtc::VideoSendTiming::kInvalid;
564
565 // FIXME: QP is ignored because there is no H.265 bitstream parser.
566
567 BOOL res = _callback(frame, [[RTCCodecSpecificInfoH265 alloc] init], nullptr);
568 if (!res) {
569 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << "Encode callback failed.";
570 return;
571 }
572 _bitrateAdjuster->Update(frame.buffer.length);
573}
574
575- (RTCVideoEncoderQpThresholds*)scalingSettings {
576 return [[RTCVideoEncoderQpThresholds alloc]
577 initWithThresholdsLow:kLowh265QpThreshold
578 high:kHighh265QpThreshold];
579}
